# /intent — Natural Language Intent Router

Owner: Any role. Decision-support command — no LLM call on the routing path.

## Purpose

Routes a free-form phrase (typed by any role) to the most appropriate
`signalos` command. Uses pure-stdlib weighted keyword matching across
10 known intents. Confidence below 0.70 triggers a clarifying question
instead of a hard route.

## Usage

```
signalos intent "<phrase>"            # human-readable route card
signalos intent "<phrase>" --json     # machine-readable JSON
signalos intent "<phrase>" --all      # show all intent scores
signalos intent "<phrase>" --threshold 0.5  # override confidence floor
```

## Exit codes

| Code | Meaning |
|---|---|
| 0 | Routed — confidence ≥ threshold |
| 1 | Low confidence — clarifying question printed |
| 2 | No phrase supplied / usage error |

## Supported intents

| Intent | Suggested command |
|---|---|
| onboard | `signalos session start` |
| brainstorm | `signalos harness call --step brainstorm` |
| plan | `signalos orchestrate --wave <id> --plan PLAN.md` |
| execute | `signalos orchestrate --wave <id> --plan PLAN.md` |
| review | `signalos harness call --step review` |
| status | `signalos status` |
| sign | `signalos sign <gate>` |
| pause | `signalos pause list` |
| resume | `signalos pause resume <step-id>` |
| compress | `signalos context compress <input-file>` |

## Routing algorithm

Keyword matching: each intent defines weighted regex patterns. The phrase
is lowercased and scored against every pattern; `confidence = raw_score / max_score`,
clamped to `[0, 1]`. The top-scoring intent wins. If confidence ≥ 0.70 the
command is printed and exit 0 is returned. Otherwise the intent's clarifying
question is printed and exit 1 is returned.

Pure stdlib — no LLM call, no network I/O.

## Implementation

`cli/signalos_lib/intent.py` — classifier library (`classify`, `top_match`, `route_or_clarify`).
`cli/signalos_lib/commands/intent.py` — CLI entry point (`main`).
`core/execution/skills/intent-router/SKILL.md` — routing decision guidance for agents.

## Next command

If routed: run the suggested `signalos` command shown in the output.
If not routed: answer the clarifying question and re-run with a clearer phrase.
